      <div id="sidebar-comp">
       <h2 class="side-header">
        News
       </h2>
       <a href="http://news.communication.ucsd.edu/assistant-professor-christo-sims-wins-book-award-from-the-american-sociological-association/">
       </a>
       <h2 class="side">
        <a alt="Link to full article" href="http://news.communication.ucsd.edu/assistant-professor-christo-sims-wins-book-award-from-the-american-sociological-association/">
         Christo Sims wins Book Award from the American Sociological Association
        </a>
       </h2>
       <article>
        <p class="p1">
         Sims's book, Disruptive Fixation: School Reform and the Pitfalls of Techno-Idealism, has been named the recipient of the 2018 Best Book Award from the Communication, Information Technology, and Media Sociology section of the American Sociological Association.
        </p>
       </article>
       <a href="https://unquote.ucsd.edu/communication/associate-professor-patrick-andersons-autobiography-of-a-disease-receives-the-2018-icqi-qualitative-book-award/">
       </a>
       <h2 class="side">
        <a alt="Link to full article" href="https://unquote.ucsd.edu/communication/associate-professor-patrick-andersons-autobiography-of-a-disease-receives-the-2018-icqi-qualitative-book-award/">
         Patrick Anderson wins 2018 ICQI Qualitative Book Award
        </a>
       </h2>
       <article>
        <p class="p1">
         Anderson's latest book, Autobiography of a Disease, has been recognized by the International Congress of Qualitative Inquiry as the "book that best represents an important contribution to qualitative inquiry" published in 2016 and 2017.
        </p>
       </article>
       <a href="http://news.communication.ucsd.edu/communication-departments-graduate-students-nalini-asha-biggs-and-caroline-collins-selected-for-san-diego-film-week/">
       </a>
       <h2 class="side">
        <a alt="Link to full article" href="http://news.communication.ucsd.edu/communication-departments-graduate-students-nalini-asha-biggs-and-caroline-collins-selected-for-san-diego-film-week/">
         Graduate Students, Nalini Asha Biggs and Caroline Collins, selected for San Diego Film Week
        </a>
       </h2>
       <article>
        <p class="p1">
         Two movies advocate for a critical analysis of cultural memory and neuronormativity
        </p>
       </article>
       <a href="http://news.communication.ucsd.edu/science-incarceration-and-racialization-a-qa-with-alum-cristina-visperas/">
       </a>
       <h2 class="side">
        <a alt="Link to full article" href="http://news.communication.ucsd.edu/science-incarceration-and-racialization-a-qa-with-alum-cristina-visperas/">
         Science, Incarceration, and Racialization
        </a>
       </h2>
       <article>
        <p class="p1">
         A Q&amp;A with Cristina Visperas, Assistant Professor at USC Annenberg and 
UCSD Department of Communication and Sciences Studies Alumna
        </p>
       </article>
       <a href="http://news.communication.ucsd.edu/new-book-enclosure-by-associate-professor-gary-fields/">
       </a>
       <h2 class="side">
        <a alt="Link to full article" href="http://news.communication.ucsd.edu/new-book-enclosure-by-associate-professor-gary-fields/">
         Gary Fields’s new book, Enclosure: Palestinian Landscapes in a Historical Mirror, featured in The New York Review of Books
        </a>
       </h2>
       <article>
        <p class="p1">
         Congratulations to Associate Professor Gary Fields on having his recently released book, Enclosure: Palestinian Landscapes in a Historical Mirror, featured in the cover story for this week’s New York Review of Books.
        </p>
       </article>
